# Cloudflare Pages redirects. Old post perma-URLs -> current slugs.
# Cover the bare path, the trailing-slash form, and any sub-paths: without
# the trailing-slash rule the /posts/pandora-desktop/ URL falls through to the
# SPA fallback and the client tries to load a route chunk that no longer exists.
/posts/pandora-desktop   /posts/jarlid  301
/posts/pandora-desktop/  /posts/jarlid  301
/posts/pandora-desktop/* /posts/jarlid  301
